==English==
===Etymology===
Reputed to be a reference to [[grey]] [[uniform]]s originally worn by parking inspectors, the term has remained even when those uniforms have changed.
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# (''Australia, or [[Melbourne]] and [[Sydney]] at least'') A parking inspector, ie. person issuing tickets [[fine|fining]] vehicles [[park]]ed illegally or for too long.
#: ''Grey ghosts turn a blind eye'' &mdash; [[w:Sydney Morning Herald|Sydney Morning Herald]] headline 18 July 1998 [http://www.walk.com.au/pedestriancouncil/Page.asp?PageID=432]
